column37: Lightly-raced 7yo was sent off at odds on for this race in 2023 but could only manage a 3.25l second; returned from a 228 day break at Navan in May last year to finish a close second on Flat handicap debut; even longer absence to overcome now.

column37: Winner on sole Flat start in a French 1m7f conditions race on very soft ground in 2021; jumping has been his kryptonite in recent chasing starts, including when pulled up in the Galway Plate last time; has been running at about 3m and even ran in the Scottish National, so may be taken off his feet at this trip.

column36: Lightly raced 9yo has a chance on ratings but may come on for the run; watch market
column37: Very lightly raced for his age and took form to a new level when winning valuable handicap hurdle at Haydock in November; Ascot Grade 1 was a bridge too far following that and hasn't been seen since weakening when a faller at Sandown in February; rated 17lb higher over hurdles than Lark In The Mornin but may come on for the run; check the market.

column37: Ballinrobe bumper winner has gone close in two similar events when losing by 0.5l both times on good ground; finished in front of Lark In The Mornin here in June when running on well and 4lb better off now; looks the pick of the stable's three runners.

column37: Smart staying hurdler, winning 3m Doncaster Grade 2 mares' event last season and ended campaign with Grade 1 placings at both Aintree and Punchestown; won 1m4f Curragh maiden last Autumn on first Flat run; unfancied and always behind in a Galway festival Listed event earlier this month; may do better with that run under her belt.

column37: Gained third win over timber in a Listed hurdle against her own sex at Killarney in May (2m1f, yielding); struggled in a Tipperary Grade 3 hurdle following that before a decent showing in a valuable Galway festival handicap hurdle last time (2m6f, good); trip versatile but a fair bit to find.

column37: In good form over hurdles earlier in the year, winning at Down Royal in January before an honourable fifth in a valuable Leopardstown handicap in February; bagged third hurdling win when taking a Punchestown festival auction race (2m3f, yielding); would need career best.
